Key Match Events: Travis Head scored 137 runs off 120 balls
Travis Head took a spectacular catch to dismiss Rohit Sharma
Australia won by 6 wickets with 42 balls remaining
Pre-Game Insights: Travis Head has matured over the last two years across all formats
Australia's irrepressible trio of quicks cement their legacy
Cummins pleased Australia'saved the best for last'
Post-Match Reflections: Travis Head was all smiles after finishing with 137 off 120 in the World Cup final
Australia's victory came at a canter in the end, with six wickets standing and a huge 42 balls unused
The closing hour of the match was greeted in stunned silence by a 92,453-strong crowd
Australia's magnificent attack could not be denied, especially after Cummins had seized on their visible reticence to smuggle through a churn of change bowlers
Miscellaneous Highlights: David Warner, in what may turn out to be his final ODI innings, had scuffed Shami's first legitimate delivery to Virat Kohli at slip for 7
Marnus Labuschagne, retained in Australia's starting XI, showed the value of his Test pre-eminence with an indomitable sidekick's role of 58 not out from 110 balls
India's Nos. 6-11 had barely been called upon in scoring a total of 240 runs between them in their previous ten tournament wins
KL Rahul endured, but was scarcely unable to unfurl either, even though he did break a 97-ball sequence without a boundary by lobbing Maxwell over his shoulder through fine leg for four
Starc, from round the wicket, straightened an unplayable delivery into Rahul's edge and through to the keeper
Suryakumar Yadav ground out 18 from 27 before lobbing Hazlewood to the keeper
The mood within the stadium was never able to emerge from its funk
Others: Rohit Sharma's shortlived onslaught was all the more brave, selfless even, as he shouldered the entire responsibility for India's powerplay proactivity
Pat Cummins backed up his brave decision to bowl first with an unhittable spell
Travis Head's catch was compared to Kapil Dev's running catch off Viv Richards at the pivotal juncture of the 1983 final
